# m6_p10_acid_feather.shot — M6 P10
#
# Tight-shot view of a single ACID zone exercising the caustic-band
# taper (§2 Part C) and the feathered green glow (§2 Part A). Run on
# Slipstream so the ICE backdrop contrasts the green well.
#
# Visual checks:
#   - Green glow has a visible bleed ~32 px past the rect edge.
#   - Caustic wave bars fade in/out at the rect's left/right edges
#     instead of cliffing.
#   - No hard rect outline anywhere.
#   - Bubbles spawn from the bottom edge, most from the inset
#     interior, ~15% from the actual edge with half alpha.
#
# Run:
#   ./soldut --shot tests/shots/m6_p10_acid_feather.shot
# Output:
#   build/shots/m6_p10_acid_feather/{wide,close_left,close_right}.png

window 1920 1080
seed   7 7
out    build/shots/m6_p10_acid_feather

map slipstream

# Place a single ACID rect at a known location. Slipstream is 100×50
# tiles → 3200×1600 px. Place the ACID zone on the floor area near
# x=1200..1600, y=1100..1280 (180 px tall × 400 px wide — wide enough
# that the caustic taper across the left/right 24 px of the inset
# range is clearly visible).
paint_ambi 2  1200 1100 1600 1280   0.6   0.0  0.0       # ACID

# Mech well outside the zone for the wide shot.
spawn_at 1400 1000
mouse    1400 540

# Wide framing — see whole zone with feathered bleed on all sides.
at 30  shot wide

# Walk through the zone for the close-up frames. Approach from left,
# then exit right.
at 30  press right
at 90  shot close_left
at 150 shot close_right
at 180 release right

contact_sheet cs cols 3 cell 640 360

at 200 end
